      "role": "user",
      "content": "hi, i was looking at my mortgage statement from wells fargo and i'm a bit confused. i have a 30 year fixed at 6.5%. i know my monthly payment stays the same, but it feels like i'm barely touching the actual loan amount in the early years. can u explain why most of my money goes to interest at first and how that changes over time? like if i look at year 5 vs year 25, what's the difference?",
